                            <comment id="294622" author="pjones" created="Thu, 11 Mar 2021 05:10:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.15&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="294485" author="gerrit" created="Wed, 10 Mar 2021 08:03:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oleg Drokin (green@whamcloud.com) merged in patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/41791/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/41791/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14477&quot; title=&quot;lnet doesn&amp;#39;t work with no IPV6 support in the kernel&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14477&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14477&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lnet: handle possiblity of IPv6 being unavailable.&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: &lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 30de2a33feae81d64cfdc7ddb76951e1fc1be916&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="293389" author="neilb" created="Mon, 1 Mar 2021 00:57:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When creating a socket to listen for new connections, the new code always creates and IPv6 socket, and requests that IPv4 connections be handled on that socket.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortuantely, this doesn&apos;t work if IPv6 support isn&apos;t available -&#160; -EAFNOSUPPORT is returned when creating the socket.&#160; So I&apos;ll have to detect that and try.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please test &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/41791&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/41791&lt;/a&gt; and report if that fixes the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="293388" author="gerrit" created="Mon, 1 Mar 2021 00:57:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Neil Brown (neilb@suse.de) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/41791&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/41791&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
